0},"title":"Hadith on Turbans: The Prophet wears a black turban","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 21, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Jabir ibn Abdullah reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, entered Mecca on the day of its liberation while wearing a black turban, without preparing to perform the pilgrimage. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1358 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u062c\u064e\u0627\u0628\u0650\u0631\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0623\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0635\u064e\u0627\u0631\u0650\u064a\u0650\u0651 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0651\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15168,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/07\/21\/prophet-shrouded-janazah\/","url_meta":{"origin":43011,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Janazah: The Prophet shrouded for his funeral","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 21, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, was shrouded for his funeral in three white cotton garments, among which was neither a shirt, nor a turban. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1264, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 941 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi (authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":13900,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/05\/02\/wiping-turban-socks-wudu\/","url_meta":{"origin":43011,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Wiping turbans and socks in ablution","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 2, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Mughirah ibn Shu\u2019bah reported: I was with the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, on a journey and I reached out to take off his leather socks. The Prophet said, \u201cLeave them, for I have worn them in a state of purity.\u201d Then, the Prophet wiped over them for\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25662,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/21\/wipe-over-socks-headgear-wudu\/","url_meta":{"origin":43011,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Wiping over socks and headgear in ablution","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 21, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Bilal reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, wiped over leather socks and head coverings in ablution. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 275 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim Ibn Taymiyyah said, \u201cSince it is permitted for men to wipe over clothing on the head, so is it\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":43164,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2025\/03\/16\/proudful-trailing\/","url_meta":{"origin":43011,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Pride: Punishment for proudful trailing clothes","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 16, 2025","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cDraping is in regards to the robe, shirt, and turban. Whoever trails any of them in pride, Allah will not look at him on the Day of Resurrection.\u201d Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 4094 Grade: Sahih\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15142,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/07\/19\/dua-new-clothing\/","url_meta":{"origin":43011,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Clothing: The Prophet\u2019s supplication for wearing new clothes","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 19, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Sa\u2019id al-Khudri reported: When the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, wore a new garment he would name it, such as a turban, a shirt, or a cloak, and then he would say, \u201cO Allah, praise be to you that you have dressed me with it.\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/43011","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\